<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The family 
<taxonomicName box="[610,716,625,649]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Rivulidae</taxonomicName>
was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Parenti LR" box="[275,431,657,681]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="341 - 557" refId="ref16301" refString="Parenti LR. A phylogenetic and biogeographic analysis of Cyprinodontiform fishes (Teleostei: Atherinomorpha). Bull Am Mus Nat Hist. 1981; 168 (4): 341 - 557." type="journal article" year="1981">Parenti (1981)</bibRefCitation>
to accommodate the new world aplocheiloids; its monophyly was supported by seven synapomorphies. Subsequent morphological (
<bibRefCitation author="Costa WJEM" box="[636,771,721,745]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="65 - 82" refId="ref13324" refString="Costa WJEM. Analise filogenetica da familia Rivulidae (Cyprinodontiformes, Aplocheiloidei). Rev Bras Biol. 1990; 50: 65 - 82." type="journal article" year="1990">Costa, 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa WJEM" box="[136,193,753,777]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="33 - 94" refId="ref13376" refString="Costa WJEM. Phylogeny and classification of Rivulidae revisited: Origin and evolution of annualism and miniaturization in rivulid fishes (Cyprinodontiformes: Aplocheiloidei). J Comp Biol. 1998; 3: 33 - 94." type="journal article" year="1998">1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa WEJM" box="[213,283,753,777]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="105 - 20" refId="ref13489" refString="Costa WEJM. Relationships and redescription of Fundulus brasiliensis (Cyprinodontiformes: Rivulidae), with description of a new genus and notes on the classification of the Aplocheiloidei. Ichthyol Explor Freshw. 2004 a; 15 (2): 105 - 20." type="journal article" year="2004">2004a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hertwig T" box="[303,471,753,777]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="141 - 74" refId="ref15210" refString="Hertwig T. Phylogeny of the Cyprinodontiformes (Teleostei, Atherinomorpha): The contribution of cranial soft tissue characters. Zool Scr. 2008; 37 (2): 141 - 74." type="journal article" year="2008">Hertwig, 2008</bibRefCitation>
) and molecular (
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy WJ &amp; Collier GE" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="790 - 99" refId="ref16050" refString="Murphy WJ, Collier GE. A molecular phylogeny for aplocheiloid fishes (Atherinomorpha, Cyprinodontiformes): The role of vicariance and the origins of annualism. Mol Biol Evol. 1997; 14 (8): 790 - 99." type="journal article" year="1997">Murphy, Collier, 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hrbek T &amp; Larson A" box="[298,531,785,809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1200 - 16" refId="ref15295" refString="Hrbek T, Larson A. The evolution of diapause in the killifish family Rivulidae (Atherinomorpha Atherinomorpha, Cyprinodontiformes): A molecular phylogenetic and biogeographic perspective. Evolution. 1999; 53 (4): 1200 - 16." type="journal article" year="1999">Hrbek, Larson, 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy WJ &amp; Thomerson, JE &amp; Collier GE" box="[544,770,785,809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="289 - 301" refId="ref16093" refString="Murphy WJ, Thomerson, JE, Collier GE. Phylogeny of the Neotropical killifish family Rivulidae (Cyprinodontiformes, Aplocheiloidei) inferred from mitochondrial DNA sequences. Mol Phylogenet Evol. 1999; 13 (2): 289 - 301." type="journal article" year="1999">
Murphy 
<emphasis box="[640,690,785,809]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
., 1999
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa WEJM" box="[136,284,817,841]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="139 - 54" refId="ref13870" refString="Costa WEJM. Historical biogeography of Aplocheiloid killifishes (Teleostei: Cyprinodontiformes). Vertebr Zool. 2013; 63 (2): 139 - 54." type="journal article" year="2013">Costa, 2013</bibRefCitation>
) phylogenetic analyses have supported a monophyletic 
<taxonomicName box="[352,462,849,873]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Rivulidae</taxonomicName>
; although the proposed synapomorphies have changed since 
<bibRefCitation author="Parenti LR" box="[565,722,881,905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="341 - 557" refId="ref16301" refString="Parenti LR. A phylogenetic and biogeographic analysis of Cyprinodontiform fishes (Teleostei: Atherinomorpha). Bull Am Mus Nat Hist. 1981; 168 (4): 341 - 557." type="journal article" year="1981">Parenti (1981</bibRefCitation>
; see 
<bibRefCitation author="Loureiro M &amp; de Sa RO" box="[136,386,913,937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="3 - 32" refId="ref15739" refString="Loureiro M, de Sa RO. Diversity of Aplocheiloidei. In: Berois N, Garcia G, de Sa RO, editors. Annual Fishes: life history strategy, diversity, and evolution. Boca Raton: CRC Press; 2016. p. 3 - 32." type="book chapter" year="2016">Loureiro, de Sá, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<tableCitation box="[439,509,913,937]" captionStart="Tab" captionStartId="2.[820,865,465,489]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Tab. 1. Synapomorphies of the family Rivulidae proposed by Costa (2004) and Hertzwig (2008)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF719F8EFFB8FF9CFC937CE9F988FB4F" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" tableUuid="DF719F8EFFB8FF9CFC937CE9F988FB4F">Tab. 1</tableCitation>
, we show the currently recognized synapomorphies of the family considering the analyses of Costa (2004) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hertwig T" box="[523,699,977,1001]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="141 - 74" refId="ref15210" refString="Hertwig T. Phylogeny of the Cyprinodontiformes (Teleostei, Atherinomorpha): The contribution of cranial soft tissue characters. Zool Scr. 2008; 37 (2): 141 - 74." type="journal article" year="2008">Hertwig (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. Costa (2004) suggested the existence of three clades within 
<taxonomicName box="[136,245,1041,1065]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Rivulidae</taxonomicName>
, and although he proposed eight synapomorphies supporting the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grote" authorityYear="1895" box="[312,418,1073,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rivulinae">Rivulinae</taxonomicName>
+ Cynolebiasinae sister group relationship, other phylogenetic analyses (combined and molecular) showed conflicting results: a basal polytomy at the origin of these clades (
<bibRefCitation author="Hrbek T &amp; Larson A" box="[421,651,1169,1193]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1200 - 16" refId="ref15295" refString="Hrbek T, Larson A. The evolution of diapause in the killifish family Rivulidae (Atherinomorpha Atherinomorpha, Cyprinodontiformes): A molecular phylogenetic and biogeographic perspective. Evolution. 1999; 53 (4): 1200 - 16." type="journal article" year="1999">Hrbek, Larson, 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy WJ &amp; Thomerson, JE &amp; Collier GE" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="289 - 301" refId="ref16093" refString="Murphy WJ, Thomerson, JE, Collier GE. Phylogeny of the Neotropical killifish family Rivulidae (Cyprinodontiformes, Aplocheiloidei) inferred from mitochondrial DNA sequences. Mol Phylogenet Evol. 1999; 13 (2): 289 - 301." type="journal article" year="1999">
Murphy 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
., 1999
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa WJEM" box="[250,395,1201,1225]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="233 - 49" refId="ref13755" refString="Costa WJEM. Phylogenetic position and taxonomic status of Anablepsoides, Atlantirivulus, Cynodonichthys, Laimosemion, and Melanorivulus (Cyprinodontiformes: Rivulidae). Ichthyol Explor Freshw. 2011 a; 22 (3): 233 - 49." type="journal article" year="2011">Costa, 2011a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa WEJM" box="[408,467,1201,1225]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="139 - 54" refId="ref13870" refString="Costa WEJM. Historical biogeography of Aplocheiloid killifishes (Teleostei: Cyprinodontiformes). Vertebr Zool. 2013; 63 (2): 139 - 54." type="journal article" year="2013">2013</bibRefCitation>
); a sister group relationship between Kryptolebiasinae + 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grote" authorityYear="1895" box="[447,553,1233,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rivulinae">Rivulinae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vermeulen FBN &amp; Hrbek T" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref16864" refString="Vermeulen FBN, Hrbek T. Kryptolebias sepia n. sp. (Actinopterygii: Cyprinodontiformes: Rivulidae), a new killifish from the Tapanahony River drainage in southeast Surinam. Zootaxa. 2005; 928 (1): 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="2005">Vermeulen, Hrbek, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Furness AI &amp; Reznick DN &amp; Springer MS &amp; Meredith RW" box="[205,425,1265,1289]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="20142189" refId="ref14726" refString="Furness AI, Reznick DN, Springer MS, Meredith RW. Convergent evolution of alternative developmental trajectories associated with diapause in African and South American killifish. Proc R Soc B Biol Sci. 2015; 282 (1802): 20142189." type="journal article" year="2015">
Furness 
<emphasis box="[297,345,1265,1289]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
., 2015
</bibRefCitation>
); and a sister group relationship between Kryptolebiasinae + Cynolebiasinae (
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl M &amp; Milvertz FC &amp; Meyer A &amp; Vences M" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="37 - 44" refId="ref16484" refString="Pohl M, Milvertz FC, Meyer A, Vences M. Multigene phylogeny of Cyprinodontiform fishes suggests continental rediations and a rogue taxon position of Pantanodon. Vertebr Zool. 2015; 65 (1): 37 - 44." type="journal article" year="2015">
Pohl 
<emphasis box="[709,761,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
., 2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa WJEM &amp; Amorim PF &amp; Mattos JLO" box="[205,414,1329,1353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="61 - 68" refId="ref14244" refString="Costa WJEM, Amorim PF, Mattos JLO. Molecular phylogeny and timing of diversification in South American Cynolebiini seasonal killifishes. Mol Phylogenet Evol [serial on the Internet]. 2017 a; 116: 61 - 68. Available from: http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2017.07.020" type="journal article" year="2017">
Costa 
<emphasis box="[274,322,1329,1353]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">et al</emphasis>
., 2017a
</bibRefCitation>
)
